==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈbʌtˌhɚt/|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{context|slang|lang=en}} Overly [[annoyed]] or [[bothered]] by a perceived insult; needlessly [[offended]].
#: ''Don't get so '''butthurt'''; it was just a joke.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{context|slang|lang=en}} [[upset|Upset]] caused by a perceived insult or injustice.
#: ''He's just full of '''butthurt''' because he wasn't allowed to join the society.''

